# Roo Code Rules for n8n-copilot Project

## Platform-Specific Commands
- Use `;` instead of `&&` as delimiter on Windows with PowerShell
- Use `Invoke-WebRequest` instead of `curl` on Windows PowerShell
- Do not use `"""` as it throws an error. Use `"""` instead

## Code Quality & Structure
- Never create a file longer than 500 lines of code. If a file approaches this limit, refactor by splitting it into modules or helper files
- Organize code into clearly separated modules, grouped by feature or responsibility
- Use clear, consistent imports (prefer relative imports within packages)
- Always check code for indent, syntax, and logic errors after responding and correct any errors

## File Management
- Files in the reference folder are for reading only. Do not edit or incorporate these files into the application. If you need these files, recreate them
- If you have multiple tool failures use write_to_file to complete your edits

## Design Guidelines
- Always keep the design minimal but good looking
- Use Context7 MCP tool to always gather latest documentation/knowledge about a library

## Mode-Specific Delegation Rules
- Orchestrator mode: Can only delegate to Code, Ask, Architect, Debug modes
- BMAD Orchestrator mode: Can only delegate to BMAD modes (BMAD Scrum Master, BMAD Analyst, BMAD Developer, etc.)